cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new variant of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) that overcomes the mode collapse problem. The paper also demonstrates the quality of the generated images using Fr\'echet Inception Distance (FID), which is a common metric used in computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper involves formulating an objective function for GAN training, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves clustering in the embedding space, which is a common topic in graph theory (cs.GR).
